09/05/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police on Friday (May 7th) arrested a suspected member of an international criminal group involved in smuggling cocaine from Peru to European countries. 
The suspect, who came from Mitrovica, was detained in Podgorica while trying to leave Montenegro. 
Several days ago, police arrested three Montenegrins suspected of cocaine trafficking, and are searching for two Serbian members of the suspected criminal group. 
(RTCG, Tanjug, Politika - 07/05/10)
